Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To know, know of, understand. Apparently a middle voice of ephistemi; to put the mind upon, i.e. Comprehend, or be acquainted with.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Tomorrow. From a derivative of the same as aer; properly, fresh, i.e. to-morrow.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: Of what sort. From the base of pou and hoios; individualizing interrogative what sort of, or which one.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
Life, both of physical (present) and of spiritual (particularly future) existence. From zao; life.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Breath, steam, vapor. From the same as aer; mist.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: Prolongation for the base of phos; to lighten, i.e. Show.
Then, thereafter, afterwards. From epi and eita; thereafter.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: From aphanes; to render unapparent, i.e. consume, or disappear.
